<appendix id="puppet-guide-ref_material">
  <title>Reference material</title>
  <para>
    In this appendix we show links to reference material
    used throughout the documentation.
  </para>

  <para>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry id="puppet-guide-ref_material-puppet-baseinfra">
        <term>git repo - puppet-baseinfra</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Git repository containing basic Linux
            infrastructure Puppet modules.
          </para>

          <para>
            <ulink
            url="https://github.com/aberends/puppet-baseinfra"><citetitle>aberends/puppet-baseinfra</citetitle></ulink>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="puppet-guide-ref_material-puppet-conf-dmsat1">
        <term>git repo - puppet-conf-dmsat1</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Git repository containing Puppet configuration
            parameters to be used on the
            <emphasis>dmsat1</emphasis> Deployment zone.
          </para>

          <para>
            <ulink
            url="https://github.com/aberends/puppet-dmsat1"><citetitle>aberends/puppet-dmsat1</citetitle></ulink>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="puppet-guide-ref_material-puppet-software">
        <term>git repo - puppet-software</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Git repository containing software used by
            Puppet for extra functions, like the Puppet
            stdlib, GPG support, Puppet lint, etc.
          </para>

          <para>
            <ulink
            url="https://github.com/aberends/puppet-software"><citetitle>aberends/puppet-software</citetitle></ulink>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="puppet-guide-ref_material-puppet-structure">
        <term>git repo - puppet-structure</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Git repository containing setup for Puppet
            structure.
          </para>

          <para>
            <ulink
            url="https://github.com/aberends/puppet-structure"><citetitle>aberends/puppet-structure</citetitle></ulink>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="puppet-guide-ref_material-puppet-tools">
        <term>git repo - puppet-tools</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Git repository containing tools used by Puppet
            to make things easier. For example, it contains
            a python tool to automatically create DNS
            resource records from the node YAML files,
            provided that enough information is put in.
            Another example is a python tool that
            automatically creates the Cobbler script for
            bare metal deployment, also based on the node
            YAML files.
          </para>

          <para>
            <ulink
            url="https://github.com/aberends/puppet-structure"><citetitle>aberends/puppet-structure</citetitle></ulink>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="puppet-guide-ref_material-libvirt">
        <term>libvirt: The virtualization API</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            libvirt is a toolkit to interact with the
            virtualization capabilities of recent versions
            of Linux (and other OSes).
          </para>

          <para>
            <ulink
            url="http://libvirt.org/"><citetitle>libvirt: The virtualization API</citetitle></ulink>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="puppet-guide-ref_material-msat-guide">
        <term>msat-guide: MSAT guide, Allard Berends,
        Disruptivefoss MSAT</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            This guide discusses how to set up a Spacewalk
            server and how to use the MSAT script to
            configure it.
          </para>

          <para>
            <ulink
            url="http://msat.disruptivefoss.org/"><citetitle>MSAT (Meta Spacewalk and Satellite)</citetitle></ulink>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

    </variablelist>
  </para>
</appendix>

